      "result": "## Project-Camiel Overview\n\n**Type:** Godot 2D game project (child-friendly educational game)\n\n### Git State\n| Item | Value |\n|------|-------|\n| Branch | `main` (protected) |\n| Remote | `origin/main` + 2 dependabot/feature branches |\n| Tags | `alpha-v0.0.1` |\n| Last commits | Main protection docs, CI quality gate, CodeQL docs, Node 24 update, community standards |\n\n### Project Structure\n- **Engine:** Godot (`project.godot`)\n- **No npm/Node.js** — not a JS project\n- **Docs:** `docs/roadmap.md` (comprehensive), `docs/project-overview.md`, `docs/development-log.md`, etc.\n- **Alpha notes:** `ALPHA_V0_0_1_NOTES.md`\n\n### Roadmap Summary\n\n**Alpha v0.0.1** ✅ Done — playable intro scene, Camiel character, basic animations, Windows export\n\n**Alpha v0.0.2** (planned):\n- Simple main menu with big Start button\n- Background music + soft sound effects\n- One collectible (star/biscuit)\n- Short spoken/written instruction\n- Finish marker\n\n**Alpha v0.0.3** (planned):\n- First educational micro-tasks (touch red block, find blue, count 1-2-3)\n- Parent/teacher notes\n- Accessibility checks\n\n**Design principles:** One idea at a time, large UI, no time pressure, no punishment-heavy failures, minimal controls.\n\n**Known technical improvements:** Code signing, GitHub Actions automated exports, title screen, version label in-game."
